expiring seasonal budgets today and request a deferred future delivery date that matches your school's reopening schedule.</li><li>Multi-School Logistics: We can distribute a single purchase order across multiple school sites. There are no extra handling fees for multi-destination distribution; you simply pay the exact carrier shipping costs we incur. Individual tracking links are provided for each destination site to ensure smooth receiving.</li><li>Shipping Costs: Shipping is calculated and quoted on a per-order basis depending on box count, dimensions, and destinations. Final shipping costs are itemized on your formal quote so they can be accurately approved on your school's official purchase order. We consolidate items whenever possible and pass our direct carrier rates straight to your district with no markup.</li></ul></div></details><details><summary>Payment &amp; Terms</summary><div class='body'><p>We structure our billing to align seamlessly with institutional purchasing workflows, public fund regulations, and standard district accounting cycles.</p><ul><li>Purchase Order Acceptance: We accept official purchase orders from approved public schools, charter networks, private academies, and government childcare agencies. A copy of your official, signed purchase order document must be uploaded to your portal or emailed to <a href='mailto:educators@mytoywagon.com'>educators@mytoywagon.com</a> to initiate production.</li><li>Institutional Payment Window: Standard terms are Net-30 from the date your order is dispatched. Extended Net-60 terms are available upon review for qualified public entities, multi-school installations, and large-scale classroom projects. Invoices are emailed directly to your designated accounts payable department and settled via check or ACH transfer.</li><li>Tax-Exempt Verification: To ensure your order is processed with zero sales tax, a valid state-issued tax exemption certificate must be linked to your portal account or attached alongside your initial quote request. Tax adjustments cannot be applied retroactively once a purchase order is finalized and invoiced.</li><li>Quote Validation Window: All itemized institutional quotes are locked and guaranteed for 45 calendar days. If your school's internal board approval process requires an extension, please contact us before the expiration date to refresh your pricing.</li><li>Invoice Matching Compatibility: Our formal invoices mirror your approved purchase order line-for-line, using identical SKUs, product descriptions, and approved shipping totals to ensure immediate, friction-free processing by your district's business office.</li></ul></div></details><details><summary>Procurement Documents</summary><div class='body'><p>To help your administrative office onboard My Toy Wagon as an approved district vendor, we maintain an up-to-date repository of standard institutional paperwork.</p><ul><li>W-9 and Vendor Profile: Our current tax documentation and corporate filing profiles are packaged together for instant download to satisfy district compliance requirements.</li><li>Certificate of Insurance (COI): Standard liability coverage documentation is available on request to verify institutional vendor eligibility.</li><li>Sole-Source Verification: For products manufactured exclusively for our catalog, we provide formal sole-source letters to simplify non-competitive procurement bids.</li></ul><p>📄 Administrative Reminder: Need our compliance paperwork to process a quote? <a href='/pages/vendor-profile'>Download our W-9 and Vendor Profile Packet here</a></p></div></details><details><summary>Replacement Parts &amp; Care</summary><div class='body'><p>Our sensory collection is designed and crafted to withstand years of active daily use in a busy classroom environment. To protect your investment and maintain the natural integrity of these heirloom materials, we recommend following these simple maintenance guidelines.</p><ul><li>Hardwood Tray Care: Button &amp; Bug trays are crafted from solid hard maple and finished with a non-toxic protective seal. To clean, simply wipe the surfaces with a damp cloth and mild soap. Never submerge wooden trays in water, place them in a dishwasher, or use harsh chemical bleach sprays, as this will damage the natural wood grain.</li><li>Therapy Dough Longevity: Análú dough is hand-blended using natural, plant-based ingredients. To prevent the dough from drying out, always store it in its air-tight wheat-straw tin immediately after play sessions. If left out overnight, kneading a few drops of water back into the dough will quickly restore its original pliability.</li><li>Artisan Wood Accents: Our wooden block sets and figures are dyed with eco-pigments and finished with natural beeswax. Color variations and natural wood knots are a normal characteristic of handmade artisan toys and do not affect structural durability.</li><li>Component &amp; Part Support: While we do not maintain a retail inventory of individual spare parts, we understand that busy classrooms experience occasional losses or accidental damage. If your school requires a specific component replacement to restore a set, please contact our support team at <a href='mailto:educators@mytoywagon.com'>educators@mytoywagon.com</a>, and we will do our best to help you find a solution based on current workshop availability.</li></ul></div></details></div>"
